-- Liverpool Directors Seek Removal of Court Order Blocking Sale to Red Sox
-- B y   B e n   L i v e s e y
-- 2010-10-13T22:21:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/liverpool-directors-seek-removal-of-court-order-blocking-sale-to-red-sox.html
Liverpool soccer club’s independent
directors said a temporary restraining order obtained by Thomas
Hicks and George Gillett and issued by a Texas District Court to
prevent a sale of the club is “unwarranted and
damaging and will move as swiftly as possible to seek to have it
removed,” the directors said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Livesey at 
 blivesey@bloomberg.net  